Add gnomad annotation test
Add gnomad annotation test

PCM1 DNP annotation issue (#156)

The main issue that this addresses is that Tumor_Seq_Allele1 wouldn't be updated when the reference allele was changed, even though in the input the mutations were identical.

Basically this:

```
8	17796381	17796383	AAC	AAC	AGT
```
became this after annotating
```
8	17796382	17796383	AC	AAC	GT
```
Now it's fixed to output:
```
8	17796382	17796383	AC	AC	GT
```
Added a few more extra test cases that were related to this

Merge pull request #125 from ao508/resolve-dbsnp-value

Resolve DB SNP RS id value

Resolve DB SNP RS id value

ColocatedVariants in the Genome Nexus response can return non-dbSNP ids, such as COSMIC ids. A regex is used to match for colocated variant ids that match the dbSNP convention (rs###). The first dbSNP id encountered is the value that will be used for populating the "dbSNP_RS" field for the record.

- Adjusted test output files for both isoforms (mskcc, uniprot)

Use POST requests for Genome Nexus annotation pipeline (#108)

Added option to run the annotation pipeline using POSTs instead of GETs when calling Genome Nexus web service.
- To enable POST requests: Add `-p <number>` to the command line arguments where `<number>` is the chunk/POST request interval size to send to GN.

- Added `AnnotationSummaryStatistics` to keep track of failed annotations, error messages, and saves error report to file if desired.
- Added unit test comparing POST response to expected protein changes from GET method
- Added circleci tests for using POSTs requests

- General refactoring and cleanup of `MutationRecordReader` and `GenomeNexusImpl`.
- Removed `verbose` option from command line.

Ignore 4 multi allele records from vcf2maf in test

Ignore 4 multi allele records from vcf2maf in test

As recommended by cyriac:

https://github.com/genome-nexus/genome-nexus-annotation-pipeline/pull/60#issuecomment-373054572

```
These mutations can be skipped for testing Genome Nexus -
mskcc/vcf2maf:tests/test.vcf@master#L18-L21 - they were meant to test
multiallelic variants given in VCF format. MAF format doesn't support
multiallelic variants, so that's a valuable test for vcf2maf, but not for
Genome Nexus.
```

Fixed how HGVSp is resolved from HGVSc.

Fixed how HGVSp is resolved from HGVSc.

When resolving HGVSp from HGVSc, the protein coordinate resolved was not always correct.

Example:
HGVSc: `ENST00000397752.3:c.3028+2T>C`
Protein change returned: `p.X1009_splice`
Protein change expected: `p.X1010_splice`

We should be rounding up the value of the resolved protein coordinate.

Merge pull request #13 from angelicaochoa/canonical-transcript-fix

Added logic for handling inframe_insertion canonical transcripts

Genome Nexus annotation pipeline updates

1. Added logic for handling inframe_insertion and deletion canonical transcripts
Some inframe_insertion cases were being missed by genome nexus when resolving protein change.

2. Added code to correctly resolve genome assembly name and variant classification
If genome nexus could not resolve a variant then these fields would be left empty instead of retaining what was in the input MAF file

3. Fixed how `MutationRecordProcessor` generates a line record to pass to the `MutationRecordWriter`
Extra tabs were being inserted at the end of the line, creating one extra field in the row relative to the MAF header

4. Added logging to `MutationRecordReader` to alert whether a variant could not be annotated
